results.wikipedia_summary: A family of birds comprising the Asian barbets, the Megalaimidae were once united with all other barbets in the Capitonidae (Short & Horne 2002) but they have turned out to be distinct. There are 26 species living in wooded areas from Tibet to Indonesia.
